commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: split application into frontend and backend
commitResults.messageBody:
- The aim of this commit is to reduce code coupling.
- The backend serves as an integrated storage and API, which is a simplified RESTful implementation.
- Communication takes place using Request and Response objects, including error codes, where object data is serialised and deserialised using the Gson library.
- There are two endpoints, /entry and /entries implemented, which is implemented as callEntryEndpoint() and callEntriesEndpoint() respectively. Together, they enable basic CRUD operations which can be expanded on in the future.

commitResults.messageTitle: EntriesEndpoint Class : Add clause for filtering by date
commitResults.messageBody:
Takes in date time strings from the incoming request and converts them
into LocalDateTime Objects before parsing them as arguments to the
EntryLog query method. This reduces code in filterBetweenDates method in
EntryLog.

RequestParams Class : Add time start and time end enums

This allows additional info about time parameters to be parsed from
commands to backend.

Entry Class : Add getDatetime method

dateTimeString is important for generating description strings while
LocalDateTime objects are needed to compare and query EntryLog for
matching entries.

EntryLog Class : Add filter by timestamp method

Since all dates here are non-null and valid (as checked in parser), the
final check is to ensure that start date is earlier than end date. If
start date is earlier than end date, all entries between the start and
end date is returned as an EntryLog object.

ViewCommand Class : Add start date and end date attribute

Since requests are instantiated in ViewCommand Class, the ViewCommand
objects should have start and end dates as attributes so that these
attributes can be parsed to the request objects.

MessageConstants Class : Add error messages

To print more specific error messages to the user.

Parser Class : Edit parseUserInput method

Identify any date specifications parsed by users using patterns.
Identified patterns will be removed from the argument String to prevent
misreading of user inputs. (Eg dates won't be read as number of entries
to output)

Add tests for new methods in EntryLog,ViewCommand and Parser Classes.

Add author tags.

All strings that match the matcher patterns will be removed from the
original user input string. As such, strings with unique identifiers
will be matched first. The view count input will be initialised as an
empty String and will be converted to MAX_DOUBLE if not specified. This
view count input will be matched last since it does not have a unique
identifier.

Classes of all entry types extends from Entry class, and constructor for each entry type  calls the superclass constructor without initialising any attribute of its own.
